periodic not working in chebop2
	neither in 1 or both directions
	chebcoeffs2 is not working
	https://github.com/chebfun/chebfun/issues/2330

N.bc for chebop2
	see .matlab/chebfun/@chebop2/set.m
	simply treats it as a single value or single 1d function
		N.lbc = N.bc restricted to domain l
		N.rbc = N.lbc
		N.ubc = N.bc restricted to domain u
		N.dbc = N.ubc
	so
		N.bc = 0; works
	and
		N.bc = @(x) sin(pi*x); works
	but can not do different ones for different directions since always the same value is assign

N.bc for chebop
	see .matlab/chebfun/@chebop/chebop.m	~line 539
	parses as a function handle
		therefore N.bc = @(x,u) [u(left)-2*u(right), u(right)-1]; works
	if everything is linear
		solvebvpLinear in linearize.m 	line 324
			adds the bc to a BC constraint linear operator L "% quite differently from N.LBC and N.RBC"
	if something is nonlinear
		wrap the linear solve in a damped newton


chebfun2 creation
	see .matlab/chebfun/@chebfun2/constructor
	relatively independent of trigx or not
		get grid points
			start with a n*n grid
			gauß elimination with complete pivoting
				(or rather the continuous analogue completeACA = Adaptive Cross Approximation with complete pivoting)
				for grid point values and increase n until error < tol
			this gives slices of points
		get function on slices
			gauß eliminiation on chebyshev coefficients until error < machine precision
		difference trigx or not
			trig uses fourier-based trigfuns instead of chebyshev polynomials for that direction
	
